    "Id": "859397",
    "ThreadId": "362567",
    "Html": "<p>For single marker tracking, you don't even need the MarkerLayout tool and the .xml file. It's for multiple marker tracking. You can simply pass the marker ID to the MarkerNode constructor for single marker tracking. I believe it's described in the user manual. Please read the MarkerNode section again.</p>\r\n<p>Ohan</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2012-07-09T14:49:29.373-07:00",
    "UserRole": "Owner",
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "859710",
    "ThreadId": "362567",
    "Html": "\r\n<p>Hey there,</p>\r\n<p>oh cool thank you very much ohanoda. I kinda&nbsp;misinterpreted&nbsp;the &quot;params&quot; parameter at first.</p>\r\n<p>so this is how it went:</p>\r\n<div style=\"color:black; background-color:white\">\r\n<pre>MarkerNode groundMarkerNode = <span style=\"color:blue\">new</span> MarkerNode(scene.MarkerTracker, 0);</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>You could just&nbsp;substitute&nbsp;the second parameter in the above constructor with an&nbsp;integer ranging (0-27) and representing&nbsp;a marker ID for one of the predefined markers stored in the following directory:</p>\r\n<p>~\\GoblinXNAv4.1\\tools\\MarkerLayout\\bin\\Debug\\raw_markers\\ALVAR&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>That's pretty much probably the quickest way to do it I guess. Just thought to share in case it could aid anyone in the future.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again&nbsp;ohanoda, great work with GoblinXNA.</p>\r\n",
    "PostedDate": "2012-07-10T08:11:00.51-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  }
